notes: Match delayed from 15 September 1996 due to rain
Waqar Younis missed a c&b chance of Dravid, while on 63 and India at 194/2.
Highest third wicket partnership for India in ODIs - between Dravid and Azharuddin 161 runs. The previous best was by NS Sidhu and M Amarnath (158 runs) against New Zealand at Sharjah, 1987-88.
Ganguly, when on 7 and Indian Total at 260/6, dropped by Saeed Anwar off Saqlain Mushtaq.
Inzamam-ul-Haq dropped by Azharuddin in the slips off Joshi, when on 25, and Pak Total at 108/2.
